#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:2
msgid "Respectful Review Comments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:4
msgid ""
":doc:`Reviewing issues and pull requests "
"</contributing/community/reviews>` is a great way to get started with "
"contributing to the Symfony community. Anyone can do it! But before you "
"give a comment, take a step back and think, is what you are about to say "
"actually what you intend?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:9
msgid ""
"Communicating over the Internet with nothing but text can pose a big "
"challenge, especially if you remember that the Symfony community is "
"world-wide and is composed of a wide variety of people with differing "
"ideas and opinions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:14
msgid ""
"Not everyone speaks English or is able to use a keyboard. Some might have"
" dyslexia or similar conditions that affect their writing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:17
msgid ""
"Not to mention that some might have a bad experience from previous "
"contributions (to other projects)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:20
msgid ""
"You're not alone in this. This guide will try to help you write "
"constructive, respectful and helpful reviews and replies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:25
msgid ""
"This guide is not about lecturing you to \"conform\" or give-up your "
"ideas and opinions but helping you to better communicate, prevent "
"possible confusion, and keeping the Symfony community a welcoming place "
"for everyone. **You are free to disagree with someone's opinions, but "
"don't be disrespectful.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:31
msgid ""
"First of, accept that many programming decisions are opinions. Discuss "
"trade offs, which you prefer, and reach a resolution quickly. It's not "
"about being right or wrong, but using what works."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:36
msgid "Tone of Voice"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:38
msgid ""
"We don't expect you to be completely formal, or to even write error-free "
"English. Just remember this: don't swear, and be respectful to others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:41
msgid ""
"Don't reply in anger or with an aggressive tone. If you're angry, we "
"understand that, but swearing/cursing and name calling doesn't really "
"encourage anyone to help you. Take a deep breath, count to 10 and try to "
"*clearly* explain what problems you encounter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:47
msgid "Inclusive Language"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:49
msgid ""
"In an effort to be inclusive to a wide group of people, it's recommended "
"to use personal pronouns that don't suggest a particular gender. Unless "
"someone has stated their pronouns, use \"they\", \"them\" instead of "
"\"he\", \"she\", \"his\", \"hers\", \"his/hers\", \"he/she\", etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:54
msgid ""
"Try to avoid using wording that may be considered excluding, needlessly "
"gendered (e.g. words that have a male or female base), racially motivated"
" or singles out a particular group in society. For example, it's "
"recommended to use words like \"folks\", \"team\", \"everyone\" instead "
"of \"guys\", \"ladies\", \"yanks\", etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:60
msgid "Giving Positive Feedback"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:62
msgid ""
"While reviewing issues and pull requests you may run into some "
"suggestions (including patches) that don't reflect your ideas, are not "
"good, or downright wrong."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:65
msgid ""
"Now, when you prepare your comment, consider the amount of work and time "
"the author has spent on their idea and how your response would make them "
"feel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:68
msgid ""
"Did you correctly understand their intention? Or are you making "
"assumptions? Whatever your response, be explicit. Remember people don't "
"always understand your intentions online."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:72
msgid ""
"Avoid using terms that could be seen as referring to personal traits "
"(\"dumb\", \"stupid\"). Assume everyone is intelligent and well-meaning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:77
msgid ""
"Good questions avoid judgment and avoid assumptions about the author's "
"perspective."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:79
msgid ""
"Maybe you can ask for clarification? Suggest an alternative? Or provide a"
" simple explanation *why* you disagree with their proposal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:82
msgid "``This looks wrong. Are you sure it's correct?`` (e.g. typo/syntax error)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:84
msgid "``What do you think of \"RequestFactory\" instead of RequestCreator?``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:86
msgid ""
"Even if something *is* really wrong or \"a bad idea\", stay respectful "
"and don't get into endless you-are-wrong discussions or \"flame wars\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:89
msgid ""
"Don't use hyperbole (\"always\", \"never\", \"endlessly\", \"nothing\", "
"\"worst\", \"horrible\", \"terrible\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:91
msgid ""
"**Don't:** *\"I don't like how you wrote this code\"* - there is no clear"
" explanation why you don't like how it's written."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:94
msgid ""
"**Better:** *\"I find it hard to read this code as there are many nested "
"if statements, can you make it more readable? By encapsulating some of "
"the details or maybe adding some comments to explain the overall "
"logic.\"* - You explain why you find the code hard to read *and* give "
"some suggestions for improvement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:98
msgid "If a piece of code is in fact wrong, explain why:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:100
msgid ""
"\"This code doesn't comply with Symfony's CS rules. Please see [...] for "
"details.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:102
msgid ""
"\"Symfony 3 still uses PHP 5 and doesn't allow the usage of scalar type-"
"hints.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:104
msgid ""
"\"I think the code is less readable now.\" - careful here, be sure "
"explain why you think the code is less readable, and maybe give some "
"suggestions?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:107
msgid "**Examples of valid reasons to reject:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:109
msgid ""
"\"We tried that in the past (link to the relevant PR) but we needed to "
"revert it for XXX reason.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:111
msgid ""
"\"That change would introduce too many merge conflicts when merging up "
"Symfony branches. In the past we've always rejected changes like this.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:114
msgid ""
"\"I profiled this change and it hurts performance significantly\" - if "
"you don't profile, it's an opinion, so we can ignore"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:116
msgid ""
"\"Code doesn't match Symfony's CS rules (e.g. use ``[]`` instead of "
"``array()``)\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:118
msgid ""
"\"We only provide integration with very popular projects (e.g. we "
"integrate Bootstrap but not your own CSS framework)\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:120
msgid ""
"\"This would require adding lots of code and making lots of changes for a"
" feature that doesn't look so important. That could hurt maintaining in "
"the future.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:124
msgid "Asking for Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:126
msgid ""
"Rarely something is perfect from the start, while the code itself is "
"good. It may not be optimal or conform the Symfony coding style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:129
msgid ""
"Again, understand the author already spent time on the issue and asking "
"for (small) changes may be misinterpreted or seen as a personal attack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:132
msgid ""
"Be thankful for their work (so far), stay positive and really help them "
"to make the contribution a great one. *Especially if they are a first "
"time contributor.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:136
msgid ""
"Use words like \"Please\", \"Thank you\" and \"Could you\" instead of "
"making demands;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:138
msgid ""
"\"Thank you for your work so far. I left some suggestions for improvement"
" to make the code more readable.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:141
msgid ""
"\"Your code contains some coding-style problems, can you fix these before"
" we merge? Thank you\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:144
msgid ""
"\"Please use 4 spaces instead of tabs\", \"This needs be on the previous "
"line\";"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:146
msgid ""
"During a pull request review you can usually leave more then one comment,"
" you don't have to use \"Please\" all the time. But it wouldn't hurt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:149
msgid ""
"It may not seem like much, but saying \"Thank you\" does make others feel"
" more welcome."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:154
msgid "Preventing Escalations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:156
msgid ""
"Sometimes when people receive feedback they may get defensive. In that "
"case, it is better to try to approach the discussion in a different way, "
"to not escalate further."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:160
msgid ""
"If you want someone to mediate, please join the ``#contribs`` channel on "
"`Symfony Slack`_, to have a safe environment and keep working together on"
" the common goals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:164
msgid "Using Humor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:166
msgid ""
"In short: Extreme misbehavior will not be tolerated and may even get you "
"banned; Keep it real and friendly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:169
msgid ""
"**Don't use sarcasm for a serious topic, that's not something that "
"belongs to the Symfony community.** And don't marginalize someone's "
"problems; ``Well I guess that's not supposed to happen? ðŸ˜†``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:173
msgid ""
"Even if someone's explanation is \"inviting to joke about it\", it's a "
"real problem to them. Making jokes about this doesn't help with solving "
"their problem and only makes them *feel stupid*. Instead try to discover "
"what the problem is really about."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:179
msgid "Final Words"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:181
msgid ""
"Don't feel bad if you \"failed\" to follow these tips. As long as your "
"intentions were good and you didn't really offend or insult anyone; you "
"can explain you misunderstood, you didn't mean to marginalize or simply "
"failed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:186
msgid ""
"But don't say it \"just because\", if your apology is not really meant "
"you *will* lose credibility and respect from other developers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/community/review-comments.rst:189
msgid "*Do unto others as you would have them do unto you.*"
msgstr ""

